# Symphony AI Server — Cline Rules
# Migrated from .cursor/rules/*.mdc — kept in sync with CLAUDE.md

## What This Project Is

AI backend for **Symphony Smart Homes**, a residential AV/smart-home integration company in Eagle County, Colorado (Vail Valley). Owner: Matt Earley. Runs on a Mac Mini M4 nicknamed "Bob."

### Repository Contents
- **OpenClaw** — orchestrator running every 5 min (email analysis, job management, follow-ups, notifications)
- **Cortex** — Bob's brain + unified dashboard at port 8102 (`/dashboard`). Memory, goals, improvement loop, digest. Replaces the old Mission Control. Every service feeds data into Cortex via `POST /remember`.
- **Bob the Conductor** — AI voice receptionist (Twilio + OpenAI Realtime API, port 8093)
- **Client Portal** — per-client status page with native e-signature (internal port 8096, no host binding)
- **Polymarket Bot** — prediction market trading (Python, port 8430 via VPN)
- **Email Monitor** — Zoho IMAP polling, SQLite dedup, POSTs classified emails to Cortex (port 8092)
- **Notification Hub** — iMessage / Telegram / email dispatcher, port 8095
- **Proposals** — proposal PDF + approval flow (port 8091)
- **X-Intake** — Twitter/X link analysis and video transcription pipeline (port 8101)

